Part 2: Improved Unit Tests
2.1 My First Simple Test
My initial answer for the expected score was 0 — incorrect. After guidance I correctly identified LOW priority = 10 points.

# My original simple test
def test_calculate_task_score():
    task = Task(title='Test task', priority=TaskPriority.LOW)
    score = calculate_task_score(task)
    assert score == 10

Improved Test — After AI Guidance
def test_low_priority_returns_base_score_of_10():
    """
    A LOW priority task with no due date, no tags,
    and TODO status should return exactly 10 points.
    LOW weight (1) x 10 = 10 base score.
    """
    # Arrange
    task = Task(
        title='Test task',
        priority=TaskPriority.LOW,
        due_date=None,
        tags=[]
    )
    # Act
    score = calculate_task_score(task)
    # Assert
    assert score == 10, f'Expected 10 but got {score}'

What Improved
•	Name describes exactly what is being tested
•	Docstring explains WHY the score is 10
•	Explicit due_date=None and tags=[] make assumptions visible
•	Better assertion message shows actual vs expected value
•	Follows Arrange-Act-Assert pattern

